        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 3:40PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 339 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a convective shower over
Pueblo Reservoir, or 7 miles west of Pueblo, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph. An isolated lightning flash may
also be possible.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Pueblo, Pueblo Airport, Pueblo Reservoir, Salt Creek, Blende, and
Pueblo West.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
